news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA orders punitive action against multiple builders
news.para: UP-RERA has ordered strict action against multiple promoters, including Mahagun and Mahalaxmi Groups, for various RERA Act violations following homebuyer complaints. Breaches ranged from misrepresenting documents and failing to issue proper allotment letters to violating orders and presenting misleading facts. The authority aims to reinforce buyer trust and transparency.

news.title: KSH INFRA & WSB Real Estate to develop 50-acre logistics park in Bengaluru
news.para: KSH INFRA and WSB Real Estate Partners, along with co-investors, are developing a 50-acre industrial and logistics park in Hosur, Bengaluru. This ₹450 crore project, launched last year, will offer 1.25 million sq ft of space and create over 1,800 jobs. WSB and co-investors hold a 74% stake in the asset-level joint venture.

news.title: Hiranandani group launches 225-acres township in Alibaug
news.para: Hiranandani Communities launched its Hiranandani Sands township in Alibaug, Maharashtra, spanning over 225 acres with a projected revenue of ₹17,000 crore. The first phase, comprising 330 units across three residential towers, recorded ₹450 crore in sales at launch.

news.title: Over 260 properties in Nagpur default on ₹442 crore tax
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation faces a severe financial crisis as 261 prime properties owe a staggering Rs 442.34 crore in property tax, with individual defaults exceeding Rs 25 lakh. This massive arrear, if recovered, could fund critical projects like the stalled Nag River Pollution Abatement Project. Activists criticize NMC's lax enforcement and political shielding of influential defaulters.

news.title: Chennai civic body collects ₹910 crore in property tax; to meet ₹1,100 crore target by Sept 30
news.para: Greater Chennai Corporation collected ₹910 crore in property tax during the first half of FY2025-26, against a ₹1,100 crore target. Officials are intensifying collection drives, leveraging digital reminders and QR code payments to meet the goal within two days. This digital push has significantly boosted recent collections, with a record over ₹2,000 crore collected last fiscal year.

news.title: YEIDA finishes allotment of 49 plots off Yamuna Expressway
news.para: Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority completed the allotment process for 49 industrial and medical device plots, attracting an estimated Rs 800 crore investment. All 37 industrial plots were allotted across various parks, while 12 out of 21 medical device plots found takers. This initiative is projected to generate nearly 3,000 jobs.

news.title: Mumbai crime branch’s SIT makes 11th arrest in CRZ map, land records forgery case
news.para: Mumbai's SIT arrested Mohammed Vasi Akhtar Shaikh, the 11th accused in a major land scam. Shaikh manipulated city survey maps and bribed BMC officials to convert protected CRZ/NDZ lands into developable plots, facilitating illegal constructions. A chargesheet exposed a widespread conspiracy involving forged maps for unauthorized development in areas like Malvani.

news.title: Supreme Court allows conditional OCs for over 450 flats in Noida Sports City
news.para: The Supreme Court has directed Noida Authority to issue conditional occupancy certificates for six residential towers in Sector 150's Godrej Nest project, offering partial relief to over 450 families. This order, following a developer's petition, is subject to ongoing legal outcomes and the completion of promised facilities, explicitly not setting a precedent for other Sports City projects.

news.title: Over 200 residents of M3M Golf Estate protest against builder in Gurugram
news.para: Residents of M3M Golf Estate protested against the builder for alleged unilateral decisions, non-disclosure of a Rs 100 crore maintenance fund, and arbitrary hikes in charges. They accused the builder of financial opacity and operating without a valid RWA for eight years. M3M refuted the claims, stating the community is managed entirely by its RWA.

news.title: Mumbai: No rent or flats’ handover in 11 years, FIR filed against Shaad Realty
news.para: A Mumbai couple, Shakir and Fatema Shah, are in limbo after a developer allegedly sold their four allotted flats worth Rs 7 crore in a redeveloped Mhada building. Despite Mhada's orders, Shaad Realty neither paid transit rent nor handed over possession. Police have filed an FIR against the developer and its director for cheating and forgery.

news.title: Gurugram: Two years on, MRG Meridian flats not handed over, homebuyers protest
news.para: MRG Meridian homebuyers protested in Gurugram, demanding possession of flats delayed by over two years. Booked in 2019, homes were due by September 2023, but buyers face financial strain paying rent and EMIs. They urged authorities to intervene, while the builder cited NGT bans for delays, claiming construction is now complete.

news.title: Sunteck Realty to launch ₹20,000 crore worth ultra-luxury homes in Mumbai, Dubai
news.para: Sunteck Realty is entering the ultra-luxury housing segment with its new 'Emaance' brand, planning two high-rise projects in Mumbai and Dubai. These by-invite-only apartments will be priced between Rs 100-500 crore, targeting a Rs 20,000 crore revenue by June next year. This marks their first international expansion.

news.title: ED attaches ₹153 crore assets of Universal Buildwell in PMLA case
news.para: The Directorate of Enforcement has provisionally attached properties worth Rs 153.16 crore belonging to ex-promoters of Universal Buildwell Private Limited. These promoters, arrested under PMLA, are accused of siphoning over Rs 1,000 crore from homebuyers and investors. Their actions led to incomplete real estate projects and significant financial losses for those who invested over 15 years ago.

news.title: Pune: Undri blaze rings fire safety system audit & maintenance alarm
news.para: Following a fatal high-rise fire in Undri, Pune's chief fire officer announced an investigation into the failed firefighting system. Societies are mandated to conduct bi-annual fire safety audits, with responsibility for functional systems resting on management. High costs and lack of awareness often hinder compliance, despite potential penalties like utility disconnections.

news.title: Bombay HC directs action against illegal deprivation of slum tenements
news.para: The Bombay High Court ordered the State Urban Development Department to create a mechanism, with the SRA CEO, to identify illegal occupants in slum redevelopment schemes. This aims to secure tenements for eligible dwellers, holding SRA officials accountable for depriving citizens. The court emphasized compliance to rectify these injustices.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to take help from NBCC to redevelop ‘unsafe’ Tulsi Niketan
news.para: Following a fatal balcony collapse, Ghaziabad Development Authority has enlisted NBCC to redevelop the dilapidated Tulsi Niketan colony. GDA requested a pre-feasibility report within a week for the project, likely a PPP model, to address the structurally unsafe buildings, with 90% deemed unfit by a safety audit.

news.title: Capgemini sells Thane campus land, buildings to Panchshil for ₹550 crore
news.para: Capgemini Technology Services India has divested its 15.38-acre Knowledge Park in Thane, including five buildings, to Prime Lohegaon Infraspaces for Rs 550 crore. This significant transaction, reflecting a broader trend of global tech firms reassessing office portfolios due to hybrid work, marks Panchshil Realty's expansion into Mumbai. The deal highlights corporates monetizing non-core assets in key urban centers.

news.title: Thane civic body takes action against 264 illegal structures; demolishes 198 of them
news.para: Thane Municipal Corporation has demolished 198 unauthorized constructions. It also removed extensions from 66 other structures. This sustained campaign began in June. The corporation registered 50 new cases of unauthorized construction. Officials review progress regularly. Citizens can check building permissions using QR codes. This action ensures proper urban development and compliance.

news.title: WeWork India to float ₹3,000 crore IPO on October 3
news.para: WeWork India is gearing up to launch its Rs 3,000 crore initial public offering (IPO) on October 3, closing on October 7. This entirely Offer for Sale will see promoter group firm Embassy Buildcon LLP and investor 1 Ariel Way Tenant Ltd offload shares.

news.title: RAY towers a model resettlement project for nation: Kerala CM
news.para: Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan inaugurated the Thuruthy housing complex, hailing it as a model resettlement project and an example of cooperative federalism. The complex will rehabilitate 398 homeless and slum families. However, a dispute emerged as Congress leaders claimed the project was designed during their previous rule, accusing the LDF of taking undue credit.
